09/11/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The EU published a recruitment notice Thursday (November 8th), reportedly seeking nearly 1,400 people for its upcoming mission in Kosovo.
These would include customs, police and judicial officials.
Interested candidates can submit applications until November 16th.
The mission is to help oversee the transfer of responsibilities from UNMIK to Kosovo authorities.
Also Thursday, KFOR Commander Xavier Bout de Marnhac reiterated that KFOR will undertake all necessary precautions to confront violence or any other attempts to destabilise Kosovo.
(Makfax, RTK, Kosovalive, Tanjug, Balkanweb - 09/11/07)
